{"geneId":"26271","symbol":"FBXO5","description":"F-box protein 5","taxId":"9606","taxname":"Homo sapiens","type":"PROTEIN_CODING","orientation":"minus","commonName":"human","chromosomes":["6"],"nomenclatureAuthority":{"authority":"HGNC","identifier":"HGNC:13584"},"swissProtAccessions":["Q9UKT4"],"ensemblGeneIds":["ENSG00000112029"],"omimIds":["606013"],"synonyms":["EMI1","FBX5","Fbxo31"],"annotations":[{"assemblyAccession":"GCF_000001405.40","assemblyName":"GRCh38.p14","annotationName":"GCF_000001405.40-RS_2025_08","annotationReleaseDate":"2025-08-01","genomicLocations":[{"genomicAccessionVersion":"NC_000006.12","sequenceName":"6","genomicRange":{"begin":"152970535","end":"152983579","orientation":"minus"}}]},{"assemblyAccession":"GCF_009914755.1","assemblyName":"T2T-CHM13v2.0","annotationName":"GCF_009914755.1-RS_2025_08","annotationReleaseDate":"2025-08-01","genomicLocations":[{"genomicAccessionVersion":"NC_060930.1","sequenceName":"6","genomicRange":{"begin":"154171829","end":"154184878","orientation":"minus"}}]}],"transcriptCount":2,"proteinCount":2,"transcriptTypeCounts":[{"type":"PROTEIN_CODING","count":2}],"geneGroups":[{"id":"26271","method":"NCBI Ortholog"}],"summary":[{"description":"This gene encodes a member of the F-box protein family which is characterized by an approximately 40 amino acid motif, the F-box. The F-box proteins constitute one of the four subunits of the ubiquitin protein ligase complex called SCFs (SKP1-cullin-F-box), which function in phosphorylation-dependent ubiquitination. The F-box proteins are divided into 3 classes: Fbws containing WD-40 domains, Fbls containing leucine-rich repeats, and Fbxs containing either different protein-protein interaction modules or no recognizable motifs. The protein encoded by this gene belongs to the Fbxs class. This protein is similar to xenopus early mitotic inhibitor-1 (Emi1), which is a mitotic regulator that interacts with Cdc20 and inhibits the anaphase promoting complex. Alternatively spliced transcript variants encoding different isoforms have been identified. [provided by RefSeq, Dec 2008]"}],"geneOntology":{"assignedBy":"GOA","molecularFunctions":[{"name":"anaphase-promoting complex binding","goId":"GO:0010997","evidenceCode":"IDA","qualifier":"enables","reference":{"pmids":["16921029","26083744"]}},{"name":"molecular function inhibitor activity","goId":"GO:0140678","evidenceCode":"IDA","qualifier":"enables","reference":{"pmids":["23708605"]}},{"name":"molecular function inhibitor activity","goId":"GO:0140678","evidenceCode":"IMP","qualifier":"enables","reference":{"pmids":["23708605"]}},{"name":"protein binding","goId":"GO:0005515","evidenceCode":"IPI","qualifier":"enables","reference":{"pmids":["11988738","12791267","16439210","16921029","17380122","17719540","18662541","23708001","26083744","27705803","32296183","33961781","40205054"]}},{"name":"protein kinase binding","goId":"GO:0019901","evidenceCode":"IPI","qualifier":"enables","reference":{"pmids":["15148369"]}},{"name":"ubiquitin ligase inhibitor activity","goId":"GO:1990948","evidenceCode":"IDA","qualifier":"enables","reference":{"pmids":["15148369"]}}],"biologicalProcesses":[{"name":"DNA damage response","goId":"GO:0006974","evidenceCode":"IMP","qualifier":"involved_in","reference":{"pmids":["17875940"]}},{"name":"SCF-dependent proteasomal ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process","goId":"GO:0031146","evidenceCode":"NAS","qualifier":"involved_in","reference":{"pmids":["34445249"]}},{"name":"negative regulation of DNA endoreduplication","goId":"GO:0032876","evidenceCode":"IMP","qualifier":"involved_in","reference":{"pmids":["17875940"]}},{"name":"negative regulation of cell cycle process","goId":"GO:0010948","evidenceCode":"IEA","qualifier":"involved_in"},{"name":"negative regulation of cellular senescence","goId":"GO:2000773","evidenceCode":"IMP","qualifier":"involved_in","reference":{"pmids":["17875940"]}},{"name":"negative regulation of meiotic nuclear division","goId":"GO:0045835","ev